to open/to start/to turn on/to boil/to write out (a prescription, check, invoice etc)/to operate (a vehicle)/carat (gold)/abbr. for Kelvin, 開爾文|开尔文[Kai1 er3 wen2]/abbr. for 開本|开本[kai1 ben3], book format

sentences.english: His mind reached after an understanding of the problem.
sentences.chinese: 他开动脑筋，想弄懂这个问题。

sentences.english: That mixture is enough to move his jeep; however, whenever the car moves, it exhales food smell.
sentences.chinese: 当车子开动时，总是会散发出食物的味道。

sentences.english: Depress this button in case of fire.
sentences.chinese: 他按下按钮开动了机器。

sentences.english: We lowered interest rates and began printing more money.
sentences.chinese: 我们降低了利率，开动机器狂印美元。

sentences.english: There are plans for more building projects in many of the Jewish suburbs.
sentences.chinese: 而以政府在犹太郊区计划开动更多的建设项目。

sentences.english: Toyota’s assembly plants reopened after being shut down for just two days.
sentences.chinese: 关门仅仅两天之后丰田的组装线就重新开动了。

sentences.english: Once under way, it was like riding along in a skip – until we reached full speed.
sentences.chinese: 车一开动就好像是在蹦跳着前进，直到加快到了全速。

sentences.english: I hurt it the very moment I was getting into the moving tram.
sentences.chinese: 我是在硬挤上已开动的电车时碰伤的。

sentences.english: In Sweden, there is a train that works mainly on cattle.
sentences.chinese: 在瑞典，就有一种主要靠牲口开动的火车。

sentences.english: Do you know how to work the machine for lifting the platform?
sentences.chinese: 你知道怎样开动机器，升起平台？

sentences.english: The worker depressed the lever to start the machine.
sentences.chinese: 工人压下控制杆开动机器。

sentences.english: The machine will start instantly you press the button.
sentences.chinese: 你一按电钮机器就会开动。

sentences.english: We got to the stine prior to train hiszheimeris disease left.
sentences.chinese: 火车尚未开动之前，我们就到了车站。

sentences.english: So I need to do something intelligent to exercise my brain.
sentences.chinese: 所以我得做点开动脑筋的事情让大脑也得到锻炼。

sentences.english: While the world is not so crowded, while the car is not actuate.
sentences.chinese: 趁世界还不那么拥挤，趁汽车还未开动。
开动脑筋，为剧本想些点子。
